##Dead Tone crash victim, Treme in an epidemic

Wechat Dingxiangwang

Function introduction, thousands of medical workers on-line home. We know the pain and pleasure of medicine. In Clove Garden, you can keep abreast of the latest information, read in-depth reports and communicate with your peers.

By Guan Hanfeng

As a doctor, you have to deal with life and death. Seen too many ill-fated heart-wrenching story, sometimes I will doubt life. But there are always some patients, in the event of great misfortune, can be pulled off a game of death. This also makes me have to marvel at the miracle of life, I want to tell you next, is such a story.

#

#The Dead Tone accident

On January 4,2020, I received a special patient in the specialist outpatient clinic, the patient himself did not come, the family with information. The patient is in a critical condition. On December 8,2019, she was comatose after an unfortunate car accident. The diagnosis was atlanto-occipital dislocation, brain trauma, mandibular fracture, hyoid fracture, rib fracture, pulmonary contusion, etc. .

After encountering the traffic accident, the patient was sent to the local hospital for tracheotomy and tracheal intubation, and other treatment by inhalation. After 20 days of treatment at the local intensive-care unit, the patient's condition stabilizes, and the patient becomes lucid enough to inhale autonomously without relying on a machine. However, due to the limited conditions of the local hospital, unable to operate, she was advised to transfer to Wuhan.

The patient's husband, a short, thin, dark man with a worried look, was insistent that his wife was getting better. He had been breathing on his own for nine days. "

I advised them to hurry to our hospital, Foshan Tongji Hospital in Wuhan, and left their contact information for the family, making an appointment to transfer the next day. Since the patient was from a poor family and the cost of intensive-care unit was relatively high, I made a decision: Since the patient was able to suck herself out of the suction machine, I transferred her to our orthopaedic ward to minimize the cost of treatment. If it gets worse, can't breathe on your own, then transfer to the ICU.

In this way, the patient arrived at the Emergency Surgery Department of our hospital around 3 pm, when she was in a fair condition, with Oxygenation remaining around 96% .

I had her committed to the orthopaedic ward. As a result of atlantooccipital dislocation, the patient's breathing function is impaired, limbs have been paralyzed, lying on the bed can only move hands and feet slightly, because of the tracheotomy, the patient can not speak. The patient was in stable condition for the first two hours after admission. But after that, things took a turn for the worse.

The patient begins to breathe hard, saturation also from 96% , drop slowly to 80% . By the time I went to see her around 9:30 p.m. , she was about 75 percent Oxygenation. The patient inhales as hard as he can, but to no avail. I had to call the ICU. There were no beds available in the ICU that night, so I called my trauma classmate, Professor Intensive-care Unit, and transferred him to the Trauma Center.

I remember that when I took her to the trauma ward with the doctor on duty, I knew in my heart that the patient was probably not going to recover. From my experience in more than ten years of practice, if a cervical trauma patients, spontaneous breathing is not good, the prognosis is relatively poor, even if the operation is difficult to recover.

To my surprise, when I went to see her the next morning, she was wide awake from the Oxygenation. She could understand me, and she could move her arms and legs a little, and her strength was about 1 + , and I was hopeful again.

For US column surgeons, if a patient is completely paralyzed and has zero muscle strength, the chances of recovery are very small. If it is not complete paralysis, the probability of recovery is relatively large, and muscle strength even if only a partial recovery, the patient's quality of life is also very meaningful.

A rare survivor

Atlas, taken from the Greek myth of Atlas (mythology) , the Titan who carried the earth. The atlanto-occipital joint is composed of the atlanto-occipital condyle and the Occipital condyle. Our large human head is connected to the cervical vertebra by a small joint (atlanto-occipital joint) .

This kind of dislocation is not rare, a foreign study found that in the case of cervical trauma deaths, about 1 / 3 of the cases are caused by atlanto-occipital dislocation.

But this kind of trauma is very rare for US doctors. And why is that? Because the vast majority of patients with atlanto-occipital dislocation die at the site of injury or during transport.

Atlanto-occipital dislocation is very unstable, during transport, or when turning over, the joint may occur further dislocation, on the spinal cord of life center compression and pull, leading to respiratory failure and death. Although the level of out-of-hospital care has improved in recent years, it is rare in the world for such trauma patients to be admitted alive.

Review the literature, there have been cases of this disease reported abroad. Almost all orthopaedic surgeons have only heard of it and have never met it, including the most frequently performed professor of Craniocervical junction surgery in the country. Theoretically, the operative protocol is atlanto-occipital joint reduction + occipitocervical fusion, but the exact details are not known: preoperative roll over, during the operation will appear breath cardiac arrest? Foreign literature is also vague, patients with good or bad prognosis.

Encounter such a hundred years of survivors, my mood is mixed, one is excited, think this situation can survive, it is not easy. Second, nervous, God let her go, and then we doctors can win this difficult game to help her out of danger?

Originally intended for surgery on Friday (January 10) , but from Friday morning, the patient began to have a fever, and then the heart-wrenching new pneumonia, has begun to open its claws in Wuhan, we can imagine the mood.

The patient has been bedridden for a month after tracheotomy. Lung infection is inevitable and the fever suggests that the infection may not be under control. The young doctor in the Emergency Department of our hospital had contracted pneumonia of unknown cause on January 6. Is it possible that our patient had a fever at this time?

We had to cancel the surgery.

100,000 reasons to quit

The patient came from a poor family in a rural area and had no health insurance. The accident was caused by a patient riding an electric scooter that accidentally hit a roadside parking lot

Before coming to my hospital, the family had already spent $200,000 on the trauma, and the family was already borrowing money. If want to undertake an operation, need to raise costly operation fee, if do not operate, rely on machine of Suction, daily cost also is about 10,000 yuan. We're Stuck in the Middle.

Even now, even if all goes well, it's GONNA cost at least $100,000. If you need to rely on breathing machines for a long time after surgery, the cost is astronomical.

In the difficult preoperative conversation, the patient's husband although anxious, but one point is very firm, that is, "must save my wife! "! If I have to have surgery, I will save her, even if I have to take care of her for the rest of her life! "

There's something special about this family.

Surgery in the shadow of an epidemic

On Wednesday, Jan. 15, the hospital's normally busy operating rooms were empty and deserted as the new year approached, as well as because of new pneumonia and gun breath. The patient account owes more than 20,000 yuan, under the support of Professor Li Feng, director of the Department of Orthopaedics at Tongji, the operation proceeded as planned.

The operation plan is atlanto-occipital joint reduction + occipitocervical fusion. For us, occipitocervical fusion is a relatively routine operation, but how to reset? The atlanto-occipital joint is adjacent to the high cervical spinal cord and contains the respiratory center. During the turning over, will the patient have cardiac arrest during the operation?

In order to ensure the safety of the patients during the operation, we asked the doctors in the support room of the rehabilitation department to make a support for the patients. The support is equal to half of the armor and covers the head, neck and upper body of the patients.

The way the patient looks in braces

The patient entered the operating room at 4 pm. Professor Yu Honghui of the anesthesiology department performed the anesthesia. The operation started at 7 pm on Wednesday. Every step of preoperative preparation and anesthesia can not tolerate a single blemish. Professor Xiong Wei, deputy director of Tongji orthopaedics department, will perform the operation. Everything seems to be going well.

On the morning of January 16, the patient was lying on a bed in the ICU on the first day after surgery, still paralyzed and covered in tubes. I went to see her as usual, but unexpectedly, on this cold winter day, the patient's swollen face burst into a stubborn smile.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Smiling face in the intensive-care unit

In all my years as a doctor, I rarely saw such a smile in the ICU. The smile relieved my nervousness and made me feel hopeful again. The treatment continued, though the bills were mounting.

The Treme of an epidemic

On January 23,2020, the city of Wuhan was under martial law as a result of a new coronavirus outbreak. The streets were deserted from their usual bustle.

The patient stayed in the ICU for a few days and everything is getting better. It's time to transfer him to the general ward. At this point, the debt has more than 80,000. I went to see her in ICU with Chen Yuan, the head nurse of the ward. Seeing the smiling patient Take My Hand tightly, Chen resisted the pressure and transferred the patient to an orthopaedic ward, with a separate room specially arranged for her.

After two days, the patient had a fever again, this time, everyone's nerves were on high alert. At this time the new crown pneumonia has spread in the hospital, our ward has a nurse teacher and a patient both confirmed the new crown pneumonia, there are 5 nurses are fever.

Because of the tracheotomy, the patient's entire lung is more exposed than normal, and the risk of infection is much higher.

The patient has a lot of sputum, and the nurse has to suck it every day. During sputum aspiration, the patient coughs irritatingly and the air rushes out. If the patient is a neopneumonitis patient, then our nurse is also susceptible to infection.

Fortunately, the patient had a CT scan of her lungs, which revealed no signs of viral pneumonia, just a bacterial infection. I repeatedly told the patient's family, must stay in the ward, strictly prohibited from leaving, in order to avoid new pneumonia. This condition occurred twice in the following two weeks, but fortunately each examination was not for new pneumonia.

At this point, although the patient's family tried everything, but the account has owed 100,000 yuan, fortunately has been gradually out of danger, began to recover slowly. She stayed in Tongji Hospital for nearly two months and remained in arrears for all but the first four days.

Now the patient has 4 + Muscle strength in all four limbs, and the tracheotomy site is slowly closing, and he can speak again. Had it not been for the outbreak, the patient would have walked out of the hospital by now.
